author: The Record
title: Ohio State will start quarterback J.T. Barrett vs. Rutgers - Sports
text:
No. 1 Ohio State will start quarterback J.T. Barrett in Saturday night's game against Rutgers, replacing Cardale Jones.
Buy this photo Ohio State quarterback J.T. Barrett, here against Penn State last week, will get the start against Rutgers on Saturday night. (AP Photo/Jay LaPrete) Coach Urban Meyer made the announcement Tuesday.
Barrett lost the starting job to Jones following a closely watched quarterback battle in the offseason for the defending national champions. But Jones has struggled to find the form that helped him lead the Buckeyes to the national title last season.
Jones has just seven touchdowns against five picks this season. He threw for just 84 yards in last week's win over Penn State.
Barrett has come on in recent weeks, with seven total touchdowns in the last two games. Meyer says red zone and third-down production were the main reasons for the switch.
